{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 6, :q-num 82, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 139641, :title "Word Chains", :problem-id 82, :answer "All 6 test cases pass (true/nil maps to true/false correctly). The solution builds an adjacency graph based on one-letter differences (substitution for same-length words, insertion/deletion for length-diff-1) and uses backtracking DFS to find a Hamiltonian path.\n\n```\n(fn [words]\n  (let [n (count words)\n        adj? (fn [a b]\n               (let [la (count a) lb (count b)]\n                 (cond\n                   (> (Math/abs (- la lb)) 1) false\n                   (= la lb) (= 1 (count (filter identity (map not= a b))))\n                   :else (let [[shorter longer] (if (< la lb) [a b] [b a])]\n                           (some #(= (str (subs longer 0 %) (subs longer (inc %))) shorter)\n                                 (range (count longer)))))))]\n    (if (<= n 1) true\n        (let [nbrs (into {}\n                         (for [w words]\n                           [w (filterv #(and (not= w %) (adj? w %)) words)]))]\n          (letfn [(dfs [cur seen cnt]\n                   (if (= cnt n) true\n                       (some #(when-not (contains? seen %)\n                                (dfs % (conj seen %) (inc cnt)))\n                             (nbrs cur))))]\n            (some #(dfs % #{%} 1) words))))))\n``", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Unable to resolve symbol: All\nData:     {:type :sci/error, :line 2, :column 1, :file \"/var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-2049737640178685740.clj\", :phase \"analysis\"}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-2049737640178685740.clj:2:31\nPhase:    analysis\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------