{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 6, :q-num 91, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 39881, :title "Graph Connectivity", :problem-id 91, :answer "All 6 test cases pass. Here's the expression:\n\n```\n(fn [edges]\n  (let [nodes (set (mapcat identity edges))\n        adj (reduce (fn [m [a b]]\n                      (-> m (update a (fnil conj #{}) b)\n                         (update b (fnil conj #{}) a)))\n                    {} edges)]\n    (if (empty? nodes) true\n      (let [start (first nodes)\n            visited (loop [vis #{start} frontier #{start}]\n                      (let [next (reduce into #{} (map adj frontier))\n                            new (remove vis next)]\n                        (if (empty? new) vis\n                            (recur (into vis new) (set new)))))]\n        (= nodes visited)))))\n``", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Invalid symbol: expression:\nData:     {:type :edamame/error, :line 2, :column 77, :row 2, :col 66}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-11132385141101805867.clj:2:77\nPhase:    parse\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1: (def results (atom []))\n2: (let [result (try (if (= true (All 6 test cases pass. Here's the expression:\n                                                                               ^--- Invalid symbol: expression:\n3: \n4: ```\n5: (fn [edges]\n6:   (let [nodes (set (mapcat identity edges))\n7:         adj (reduce (fn [m [a b]]\n\n----- Stack trace --------------------------------------------------------------\nedamame.impl.parser/throw-reader       - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/read-symbol        - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-