{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 3, :q-num 94, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 96172, :title "Game of Life", :problem-id 94, :answer "All 3 tests pass. Here's the expression:\n\n```clojure\n(fn [board]\n  (let [rows (count board)\n        cols (count (first board))\n        alive? (fn [r c] (= \\# (get-in board [r c] \\space)))\n        neighbors (for [dr [-1 0 1] dc [-1 0 1] :when (not= [dr dc] [0 0])] [dr dc])\n        count-live (fn [r c] (count (filter #(apply alive? (map + [r c] %)) neighbors)))\n        next-cell (fn [r c]\n                    (let [n (count-live r c) live (alive? r c)]\n                      (if (or (and live (#{2 3} n)) (and (not live) (= 3 n))) \\# \\space)))]\n    (mapv #(apply str %) (for [r (range rows)] (for [c (range cols)] (next-cell r c))))))\n``", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Invalid symbol: expression:\nData:     {:type :edamame/error, :line 2, :column 67, :row 2, :col 56}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-1312617782484305874.clj:2:67\nPhase:    parse\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1: (def results (atom []))\n2: (let [result (try (if (= (All 3 tests pass. Here's the expression:\n                                                                     ^--- Invalid symbol: expression:\n3: \n4: ```clojure\n5: (fn [board]\n6:   (let [rows (count board)\n7:         cols (count (first board))\n\n----- Stack trace --------------------------------------------------------------\nedamame.impl.parser/throw-reader       - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/read-symbol        - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-to-delimiter - <built-in>\n... (ru