{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 6, :q-num 106, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 193742, :title "Number Maze", :problem-id 106, :answer "Looking at this problem, I need BFS to find the shortest path between two numbers using operations: double, halve (even only), and add 2.\n\nLet me verify the expected behavior:\n- `(= 1 (__ 1 1))` — path length counts nodes (start=end, so 1 node)\n- `(= 3 (__ 3 12))` — 3→6→12 = 3 nodes ✓\n- `(= 9 (__ 9 2))` — 9→11→22→24→12→6→8→4→2 = 9 nodes ✓\n\nSo it's counting nodes in the path, not operations.\n\n```\n(fn [s e]\n  (if (= s e) 1\n    (loop [q (conj clojure.lang.PersistentQueue/EMPTY [s 1]) seen #{s}]\n      (let [[v d] (peek q)]\n        (if (= v e) d\n          (let [nbrs (distinct (remove #(or (contains? seen %) (<= % 0) (> % 1000000))\n                                      (concat [(+ v 2) (* v 2)]\n                                              (when (even? v) [(/ v 2)]))))]\n            (recur (reduce #(conj %1 [%2 (inc d)]) (pop q) nbrs)\n                   (into seen nbrs))))))))\n``", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Invalid symbol: operations:\nData:     {:type :edamame/error, :line 2, :column 128, :row 2, :col 117}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-10596914860337871817.clj:2:128\nPhase:    parse\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1: (def results (atom []))\n2: (let [result (try (if (= 1 (Looking at this problem, I need BFS to find the shortest path between two numbers using operations: double, halve (even only), and add 2.\n                                                                                                                                  ^--- Invalid symbol: operations:\n3: \n4: Let me verify the expected behavior:\n5: - `(= 1 (__ 1 1))` — path length counts nodes (start=end, so 1 node)\n6: - `(= 3 (__ 3 12))` — 3→6→12 = 3 nodes ✓\n7: - `(= 9 (__ 9 2))` — 9→11→22→24→12→6→8→4→2 = 9 nodes ✓\n\n----- Stack trace --------------------------------------------------------------\nedamame.impl.parser/throw-reader       - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/read-symbol        - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-to-delimiter - <built-in>\n... (run with --debug to see elided elements)\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-to-delimiter - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-list         - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-in>\nedamame.core/parse-next                - <built-in>"}], :run-id "4clojure-pi-blockether-glm-5-turbo-2026-04-03T17-01-38.700027Z", :model "blockether/glm-5-turbo"}
