{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 5, :q-num 110, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 120735, :title "Crossword puzzle", :problem-id 111, :answer "All 5 test cases pass. Here's the solution:\n\n```\n(fn [word board]\n  (let [w (.toLowerCase word)\n        len (count w)\n        grid (mapv #(vec (clojure.string/lower-case (clojure.string/replace % #\"\\s\" \"\"))) board)\n        rows (count grid)\n        cols (count (first grid))\n        g (fn [r c] (when (and (<= 0 r (dec rows)) (<= 0 c (dec cols))) (get-in grid [r c])))\n        ok (fn [sr sc dr dc]\n             (let [cs (mapv #(g (+ sr (* % dr)) (+ sc (* % dc))) (range len))]\n               (and (every? some? cs)\n                    (not-any? #(= \\# %) cs)\n                    (every? true? (map #(or (= %1 \\_) (= %1 %2)) cs w))\n                    (let [b (g (- sr dr) (- sc dc))] (or (nil? b) (= \\# b)))\n                    (let [a (g (+ sr (* len dr)) (+ sc (* len dc)))] (or (nil? a) (= \\# a))))))]\n    (boolean\n      (or (some #(some (fn [c] (ok % c 0 1)) (range (inc (- cols len)))) (range rows))\n          (some #(some (fn [r] (ok r % 1 0)) (range (inc (- rows len)))) (range cols))))))\n``", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Invalid symbol: solution:\nData:     {:type :edamame/error, :line 2, :column 76, :row 2, :col 67}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-4534733299224749051.clj:2:76\nPhase:    parse\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1: (def results (atom []))\n2: (let [result (try (if (= true  (All 5 test cases pass. Here's the solution:\n                                                                              ^--- Invalid symbol: solution:\n3: \n4: ```\n5: (fn [word board]\n6:   (let [w (.toLowerCase word)\n7