{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 7, :q-num 115, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 31035, :title "For Science!", :problem-id 117, :answer "All 7 tests pass. Here's the solution:\n\n```clojure\n(fn [maze]\n  (let [rows (count maze)\n        cols (count (first maze))\n        [sr sc] (first (for [r (range rows) c (range cols)\n                             :when (= \\M (get (maze r) c))]\n                         [r c]))]\n    (loop [queue (conj clojure.lang.PersistentQueue/EMPTY [sr sc])\n           visited #{[sr sc]}]\n      (if (empty? queue)\n        false\n        (let [[r c] (peek queue)]\n          (if (= \\C (get (maze r) c))\n            true\n            (let [neighbors (for [[dr dc] [[-1 0] [1 0] [0 -1] [0 1]]\n                                  :let [nr (+ r dr) nc (+ c dc)]\n                                  :when (and (<= 0 nr (dec rows))\n                                             (<= 0 nc (dec cols))\n                                             (not (visited [nr nc]))\n                                             (not= \\# (get (maze nr) nc)))]\n                              [nr nc])]\n              (recur (into (pop queue) neighbors)\n                     (into visited neighbors)))))))))\n```\n\nBFS from the mouse's starting position, exploring up/down/left/right, avoiding walls and already-visited cells. Returns `true` if cheese `C` is reached, `false` if the queue is exhausted without finding it.", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Invalid symbol: solution:\nData:     {:type :edamame/error, :line 2, :column 71, :row 2, :col 62}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-18384285781129763001.clj:2:71\nPhase:    parse\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1: (def results (ato