{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 1, :q-num 122, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 174249, :title "Gus' Quinundrum", :problem-id 125, :answer "Looking at this problem, I need to analyze the test form carefully:\n\n```clojure\n(= (__ '(fn [x] (__ x x)) '(fn [x] (__ x x)))\n   ((fn [x] (__ x x)) '(fn [x] (__ x x))))\n```\n\nThis is a quine pattern where `__` is called with **two** identical arguments, and the result must equal calling the generated `(fn [x] (__ x x))` with one argument.\n\nThe `__` inside quotes is just a symbol (data), while the outer `__` is the actual function call.\n\nLet me trace through with `F = (fn [s & _] (list 'fn '[x] (list s s)))`:\n- `Q = '(fn [x] (F x x))` (the quoted source)\n- Left: `(F Q Q)` → `(list 'fn '[x] (list Q Q))` → `(fn [x] (Q Q))`\n- Right: `((fn [x] (F x x)) Q)` → x=Q → `(F Q Q)` → same result ✓\n\nThe `& _` rest-arg is needed because `__` is called with 2 arguments in the test.\n\n`(fn [s & _] (list 'fn '[x] (list s s)))", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Invalid symbol: carefully:\nData:     {:type :edamame/error, :line 2, :column 94, :row 2, :col 84}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-11843338060182546234.clj:2:94\nPhase:    parse\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1: (def results (atom []))\n2: (let [result (try (if (= (Looking at this problem, I need to analyze the test form carefully:\n                                                                                                ^--- Invalid symbol: carefully:\n3: \n4: ```clojure\n5: (= (__ '(fn [x] (__ x x)) '(fn [x] (__ x x)))\n6:    ((fn [x] (__ x x)) '(fn [x] (__ x x))))\n7: ```\n\n----- Stack trace --------------------------------------------------------------\nedamame.impl.parser/throw-reader       - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/read-symbol        - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-to-delimiter - <built-in>\n... (run with --debug to see elided elements)\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-to-delimiter - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-list         - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-in>\nedamame.core/parse-next                - <built-in>"}], :run-id "4clojure-pi-blockether-glm-5-turbo-2026-04-03T17-01-38.700027Z", :model "blockether/glm-5-turbo"}
