{:correct? false, :passed 0, :total-tests 7, :q-num 147, :bench "4clojure", :mode :pi, :type :result, :duration-ms 87985, :title "Infinite Matrix", :problem-id 168, :answer "All 7 tests pass. Here's the solution:\n\n```clojure\n(fn\n  ([f]\n   (letfn [(row [i j] (lazy-seq (cons (f i j) (row i (inc j)))))\n           (matrix [i] (lazy-seq (cons (row i 0) (matrix (inc i)))))]\n     (matrix 0)))\n  ([f m n]\n   (letfn [(row [i j] (lazy-seq (cons (f i j) (row i (inc j)))))\n           (matrix [i] (lazy-seq (cons (row i n) (matrix (inc i)))))]\n     (matrix m)))\n  ([f m n s t]\n   (letfn [(row [i j cnt] (if (zero? cnt) () (cons (f i j) (row i (inc j) (dec cnt)))))]\n     (loop [i m cnt-s s result []]\n       (if (zero? cnt-s)\n         result\n         (recur (inc i) (dec cnt-s) (conj result (row i n t))))))))\n```\n\nThe approach:\n- **1-arg**: Builds infinite rows via `lazy-seq` + `cons` + recursion, and an infinite sequence of rows the same way, starting at `(0,0)`\n- **3-arg**: Same lazy structure but rows start at column `n` and the row sequence starts at row `m`\n- **5-arg**: Uses `loop`/`recur` to collect exactly `s` finite rows, each with `t` entries\n\nNo restricted functions (`for`, `range`, `iterate`, `repeat`, `cycle`, `drop`) are used — only `lazy-seq`, `cons`, `inc`, `dec`, `letfn`, `loop`, and `recur`.", :iterations nil, :error nil, :tokens nil, :cost nil, :failures [{:error "bb: ----- Error --------------------------------------------------------------------\nType:     clojure.lang.ExceptionInfo\nMessage:  Invalid symbol: solution:\nData:     {:type :edamame/error, :line 2, :column 90, :row 2, :col 81}\nLocation: /var/folders/67/5js7xvyn2t14v8zq9rrzb8m40000gn/T/4clj-bench-3071582280951978110.clj:2:90\nPhase:    parse\n\n----- Context ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1: (def results (atom []))\n2: (let [result (try (if (= (take 5 (map #(take 6 %) (All 7 tests pass. Here's the solution:\n                                                                                            ^--- Invalid symbol: solution:\n3: \n4: ```clojure\n5: (fn\n6:   ([f]\n7:    (letfn [(row [i j] (lazy-seq (cons (f i j) (row i (inc j)))))\n\n----- Stack trace --------------------------------------------------------------\nedamame.impl.parser/throw-reader       - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/read-symbol        - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-to-delimiter - <built-in>\n... (run with --debug to see elided elements)\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-to-delimiter - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-list         - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/dispatch           - <built-in>\nedamame.impl.parser/parse-next         - <built-in>\nedamame.core/parse-next                - <built-in>"}], :run-id "4clojure-pi-blockether-glm-5-turbo-2026-04-03T17-01-38.700027Z", :model "blockether/glm-5-turbo"}
